What insurance do I need?
Car insurance, which covers drivers in the face of possible losses, involves a significant expenditure which will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, length of driving licence, civil status, type of vehicle to be insured or use of the vehicle, among others.
Having a car is the main thing.
Y es que, escoger el seguro de automóvil adecuado es incluso más difícil que elegir el modelo de vehículo.
And it's that, choosing the right car insurance, is even more difficult than choosing the model of the vehicle.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurer.
This compromise takes the form of an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the premium granted and in return becomes responsible for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a disaster.
The premium is the price of insurance, which takes into account various factors, such as age, sex, length of driving licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or use of the vehicle, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices on the basis of statistics, so that the higher the probability of an accident, the higher the rating to be paid.
It is for this reason that people over the age of 25 and women must pay lower premiums, since the statistics show that these people have a lower rate of claims due to their prudence.
Similarly, using censuses, the companies concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will affect the frequency, and thus the likelihood of an accident.
By increasing the frequency the probabilities increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when determining the premium price.
This is why the driver needs to study the situation well in order to choose the car insurance that best fits his profile.
Here we will present the most significant variables when choosing one or the other type of insurance, so that the insurer, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insurer, offers it a reasonable price.
Young people under 25 years of age face various disadvantages when entering into an insurance contract at an accessible price, as may be the lack of experience in driving and the seniority of the driving licence.
Although the ideal to be well insured is insurance at any risk, other, more economical options exist.
The most forward-looking drivers can opt for risk-free insurance so that they get insurance coverage at any risk but at a more affordable price.
This form of agreement implies that the customer pays part of the amount of the claim.
"The part of the amount of the loss that the customer pays will be based on the value of the premium, which will be higher plus the amount will be lower," says Luis Noguera, the head of First Europa in Spain, online insurance mediator.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer provides protection to deal with damage caused to third parties, but by those caused on his own car.
In addition, it would be covered against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
A piece of advice.
If you are under 25 years of age try to be careful and avoid losses as far as possible, since this will affect the bonus, which may reduce the price of insurance in the future.
A rebate is a reduction in the company's basic rate.
On the contrary, a penalty is an increase in the basic tariff.
"Subsidies and sanctions will depend on the company and its profit.
If the company has had a good year it will be able to afford to increase the subsidies, "clarified Noguera.
After the age of 25, it becomes easier for drivers when they enter into a contract with insurance, since the loss rate is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
It is for this reason that it is preferable to choose all-risk insurance with a franchise.
"Normally young people cannot take advantage of the experience acquired in advance after an accident," says the director of the European company in Spain and adds that the majority of accidents occur during the second year of driving, once the 'fear of the novice' has passed.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is preferable for the client to negotiate insurance at any risk, as long as his or her economic situation permits.
Child marriages are considered by insurers to be the people with the lowest claim rate, because the increases will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be any risk insurance with a deductible (possibly EUR 300), or extended third-party insurance from the third year of life of the vehicle when the insured has a high level of bonus.
"They have more casual driving and greater purchasing power to afford the luxury of taking on more franchises," Judge Luis Noguera.
For pensioners, any-risk insurance with a deductible is preferable (i.e. 150 euros), or extended third-party insurance where the insurer has a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is important, not only because it covers the driver in the face of possible losses, but also because it represents an important expense, it is for this reason that it is essential to study properly the insurance that suits us most according to our personal situation.
